[DERIVED] Analysis Dataset of Adverse Events

Source: R/data.R
ADAE.Rd

Analysis dataset of adverse events derived dataset.

Usage

data(ADAE)

Format

A data frame with 3495 observations and 62 variables.

Source

For more details see the help vignette: vignette(topic = 'ADNIMERGE2-Analysis-Data', package = 'ADNIMERGE2')

Details

  • STUDYID character Study Identifier , with character options: ADNI

  • USUBJID character Unique Subject Identifier

  • SUBJID character Subject Identifier for the Study

  • SITEID character Study Site Identifier

  • TRTA character Actual Arm

  • TRTP character Planned Arm

  • AGE numeric Age (in Years) Range value: 50.5, ..., 90.3

  • AGEU character Age Units , with character options: Years

  • AGEGR1 character Pooled Age Group 1 , with character options: >=65, <65

  • AGEGR1N numeric Pooled Age Group 1 (N) Range value: 1, ..., 2

  • SEX character Sex , with character options: Female, Male

  • RACE factor Race , with factor levels: American Indian or Alaskan Native, Asian, Black or African American, Native Hawaiian or Other Pacific Islander, Other Pacific Islander, White, More than one race, Unknown

  • RACEN numeric Race (N) Range value: 1, ..., 999

  • ETHNIC character Ethnicity , with character options: Not Hispanic or Latino, Hispanic or Latino, Unknown

  • DX factor Baseline Diagnostics Status , with factor levels: CN, MCI, DEM

  • ENRLFL character Enrolled Population Flag , with character options: Yes, No

  • ENRLDT Date Date of Enrollment Date: YYY-MM-DD

  • EOSDT Date End of Study Date Date: YYY-MM-DD

  • EOSDTF character End of Study Date Imputation Flag , with character options: M

  • ASTDT Date Analysis Start Date Date: YYY-MM-DD

  • ASTDTF character Analysis Start Date Imputation Flag

  • ASTDY numeric Analysis Start Relative Day Range value: -4327, ..., 6929

  • AENDT Date Analysis End Date Date: YYY-MM-DD

  • AENDTF character Analysis End Date Imputation Flag

  • AENDY numeric Analysis End Relative Day Range value: -133, ..., 337328

  • ADURN numeric Adverse Events Duration (N) Range value: -363, ..., 332062

  • ADURU character Analysis Duration Unit , with character options: days

  • AETERM character Reported Term for the Adverse Event

  • AELLT character Lowest Level Term

  • AELLTCD character Lowest Level Term Code

  • AEDECOD character Dictionary-Derived Term

  • AEPTCD character Preferred Term Code

  • AEHLT character High Level Term

  • AEHLTCD character High Level Term Code

  • AEHLGT character High Level Group Term

  • AEHLGTCD character High Level Group Term Code

  • AESOC character Primary Sytem Organ Class

  • AESOCCD character Primary Sytem Organ Class Code

  • AESEV character Severity/Intensity , with character options: Moderate, Severe, Mild

  • AESER character Serious Event , with character options: No, Yes

  • AESCONG character Congenital Anomaly or Birth Defect , with character options: No

  • AESDISAB character Persist or Signif Disability/Incapacity , with character options: No, Yes

  • AESDTH character Results in Death , with character options: Yes, No

  • AESHOSP character Requires or Prologns Hospitalization , with character options: No, Yes

  • AESLIFE character Is Life Threating , with character options: Yes, No

  • AESMIE character Other Medically Important Serious Event , with character options: No, Yes

  • AERELCM character Related to Concomitant Therapy , with character options: Not related, Unlikely, Possibly, Definitely, Probably

  • AERELFLRBTBN character Related to Florbetaben Tracer , with character options: Not related, Unlikely, Definitely, Possibly

  • AERELFLRBPR character Related to Florbetapir Tracer , with character options: Not related, Unlikely, Possibly, Probably

  • AEHIMG character Related to PET/MRI Imaging Procedure , with character options: Not related, Possibly, Unlikely, Definitely, Probably

  • AERELTAU character Related to Flotaucipir Tracer , with character options: Not related, Possibly, Probably, Unlikely

  • AERELNAV character Related to NAV-4694 Tracer , with character options: Not related, Definitely, Possibly

  • AERELMK character Related to MK-6240 Tracer , with character options: Not related, Unlikely

  • AERELPI character Related to PI-2620 Tracer , with character options: Not related

  • AEHLUMB character Related to Lumbar Puncture , with character options: Not related, Definitely, Probably, Unlikely, Possibly

  • AERELCOVID character Related to COVID-19 Illness , with character options: Unlikely, Not related, Definitely (Confirmed COVID-19 test), Probably, Possibly

  • AERELPAN character Related to COVID-19 Pandemic Disruption , with character options: Not related, Definitely, Probably, Unlikely, Possibly

  • AERELAD character Related to Early Stage/Progression of AD , with character options: Not related, Unlikely, Possibly, Probably, Definitely

  • AERELATESP character Related to Other Study Procedure(s) , with character options: Not related, Unlikely, Probably, Definitely, Possibly

  • AECONTRT character Concomitant or Additional Trtmnt Given , with character options: Yes, No

  • AEOUT character Outcome of Adverse Event , with character options: Recovered/Resolved, Fatal, Not recovered/Not resolved, Recovering/Resolving, Recovered/Resolved with sequelae, Unknown

  • AESEQ integer Sequence Number Range value: 1, ..., 32
